# BikeSafetyESP BLE Receiver

This folder contains the simplest ESP32 BLE test firmware for the bicycle safety prototype.

It uses the official ESP32 Arduino BLE library, not NimBLE.

## Hardware

- ESP32-WROOM-32E
- Arduino IDE
- ESP32 Arduino Core 3.3.10

## What It Does

The ESP32:

- advertises as `BikeSafetyESP`
- accepts one BLE connection
- exposes one writable characteristic
- receives exactly one byte from the Android app
- prints the decoded value to Serial

It does not control vibration motors, LEDs, or any other hardware.

## BLE Protocol

Service UUID:

```text
12345678-1234-1234-1234-1234567890ab
```

Characteristic UUID:

```text
87654321-4321-4321-4321-ba0987654321
```

Payload:

| Value | Serial Output |
| ----: | ------------- |
| 0 | `SAFE` |
| 1 | `APPROACHING` |
| 2 | `DANGER` |

The Android app should send one byte whenever the threat level changes.

## How To Use

Open `example.ino` in the Arduino IDE and upload it to the ESP32.

Use these serial monitor settings:

- baud rate: `115200`
- line ending: any

Expected startup output:

```text
Boot
Initializing BLE
BLE initialized
Creating server
Server created
Creating service
Service created
Creating characteristic
Characteristic created
Starting service
Service started
Starting advertising
Advertising started as BikeSafetyESP
Waiting for phone...
READY
```

Expected output after Android writes threat values:

```text
Connected
Characteristic written
Payload received, length=1
Raw byte: 0
Threat decoded: SAFE
Characteristic written
Payload received, length=1
Raw byte: 1
Threat decoded: APPROACHING
Characteristic written
Payload received, length=1
Raw byte: 2
Threat decoded: DANGER
```

On disconnect, the ESP32 requests advertising restart and restarts it from `loop()`.
This keeps the BLE callback small and makes disconnect/reconnect behavior easier to debug.

## Android Compatibility

The Android app already uses the matching UUIDs in:

```text
android/YOLOv8-Object-Detector-Android-Tflite/app/src/main/java/com/surendramaran/yolov8tflite/ble/BleConstants.kt
```

Do not change these UUIDs unless you change both Android and ESP32 together.
